{
  "url": "https://www.nps.gov/grca/planyourvisit/rv.htm",
  "title": "Visiting the South Rim in an RV or Pulling a Trailer - Grand Canyon National Park (U.S. National Park Service)",
  "html": "<body class=\"ParkSite\"><span aria-label=\"Top of page\" id=\"__topdoc__\" role=\"navigation\"></span>\n\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div id=\"beforeSkipLinks\" tabindex=\"-1\"></div>\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div class=\"GlobalHeader usaGlobalHeader\" role=\"banner\">\n\n</div>\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<div aria-hidden=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"exitModalLabel\" class=\"modal refreshableModal\" id=\"myModal\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n<div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n<div class=\"modal-content\">\n<div class=\"modal-header\">\n<h2 class=\"modal-title visually-hidden\" id=\"exitModalLabel\">Exiting nps.gov</h2>\n<button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"></button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"modal-body\"></div>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Schedule\" id=\"cs_control_481716\"><div id=\"CS_Element_BannerContainer\" title=\"\"><div class=\"cs_GridRow\" id=\"gridRow_1_1_481716\"><div class=\"cs_GridColumn\" id=\"gridCol_1_1_1_1_481716\"><div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_CustomCF\" id=\"cs_control_828672\"><div id=\"CS_CCF_5488468_828672\">\n\n</div></div><div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_CustomCF\" id=\"cs_control_481828\"><div id=\"CS_CCF_5488468_481828\"> </div></div></div></div></div></div>\n<div id=\"Park-header\">\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"pull-left\">\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n\n</div>\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div aria-label=\"Alerts Notification\" class=\"AlertsNotification\" data-site-code=\"grca\" id=\"AlertsNotification\" role=\"dialog\">\n<div aria-live=\"polite\" class=\"AlertsNotification__Status visually-hidden\" role=\"status\">Loading alerts</div>\n<div class=\"collapse\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Panel\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Header\">\n<h2 class=\"Tag\" id=\"AlertsNotificationHeading\">Alerts In Effect</h2>\n<button aria-label=\"Dismiss\" class=\"AlertsNotification__DismissButton\" type=\"button\">\nDismiss\n<svg class=\"usa-icon\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"presentation\">\n<use href=\"/theme/assets/vendor/npsds/packages/icons/dist/sprite.svg#close\"></use>\n</svg>\n</button>\n<span class=\"hr clearfix\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Body\" id=\"AlertsNotificationBody\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__MoreLinkContainer\">\n<svg class=\"usa-icon\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"presentation\">\n<use href=\"/theme/assets/vendor/npsds/packages/icons/dist/sprite.svg#add\"></use>\n</svg>\n<a class=\"AlertsNotification__MoreLink\" href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/conditions.htm\" id=\"AlertsNotificationMoreLink\" tabindex=\"-1\">\nmore information on current conditions...\n</a>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"MainContent\" id=\"main\" role=\"main\">\n\n<div aria-labelledby=\"modal-contact-us-label\" class=\"modal fade\" id=\"modal-contact-us\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n<div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n<div class=\"modal-content\">\n<div class=\"modal-header\">\n<h4 class=\"modal-title visually-hidden\" id=\"modal-contact-us-label\">Contact Us</h4>\n<button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"></button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"modal-body\">\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"adminTools\"></div>\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"ColumnGrid row\">\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div class=\"container\">\n\n</div>\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<div class=\"ColumnMain col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"ContentHeader text-content-size\">\n<h1 class=\"page-title\">Visiting the South Rim in an RV or Pulling a Trailer</h1>\n</div>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Layout\" id=\"cs_control_2\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"CS_Layout_Table\" id=\"cs_idLayout2\" summary=\"\" width=\"100%\"><tr class=\"CS_Layout_TR\"><td class=\"CS_Layout_TD\" id=\"cs_idCell2x1x1\">\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5488549\"><div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup CaptionedImage\">\n<figure class=\"-auto-width\">\n<img alt=\"a large white RV is stationary with a red car in tow.. Two people are disconnecting the car from the RV. This is in front of a brown campground office.\" src=\"/grca/planyourvisit/images/rv-pull-car-cg-office-Fleet.jpg?maxwidth=1300&amp;maxheight=1300&amp;autorotate=false&amp;format=webp\" title=\"a large white RV is stationary with a red car in tow.. Two people are disconnecting the car from the RV. This is in front of a brown campground office.\"/>\n<figcaption>Grand Canyon National Park has limited parking and camping options for oversized vehicles - RVs over 22 feet long, and vehicle-trailer combinations with a total length over 22 feet. This webpage offers suggestions to make it easier for you to find the available oversize parking. NPS/Rita Fleet </figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_6821723\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6821723\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<p><em><a href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/grand-canyon-national-park-public-health-update.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6397341,/grca/planyourvisit/grand-canyon-national-park-public-health-update.htm,11006|\" onmouseout=\"\" onmouseover=\"\">Visit this webpage</a><span style=\"color:null;\"><strong> (updated daily) for the current list of what is open, along with hours of operation. </strong></span></em></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5488469\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5488469\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h2>Finding RV parking on the South Rim</h2>\n<p><strong>Wanting to stay overnight?</strong> <strong><a href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/cg-sr.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=1954247,cg-sr.htm,11006|\">Tent and RV Campgound information &gt;</a></strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Our busy times are spring break, summer, and weekends during fall and winter holidays.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Parking is at a premium on the South Rim</strong> when it’s busy, especially for <strong>RVs over 22 feet</strong> and for <strong>vehicles with trailers</strong>, which have limited parking options.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Grand Canyon National Park does not charge parking fees. There are no pay lots.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5488523\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<a id=\"before930\"></a><a id=\"CP_JUMP_5488523\"></a><div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5488523\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h2><span style=\"color:#000000;\">Arrive Before 9:30 am - Driving into the Village Developed Area </span></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>To find a good RV parking spot, arrive on the South Rim early – before 9:30 am</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Use the map below to find one of the 3 RV parking lots shown in the map below.</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5488506\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5488506\"><div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup CaptionedImage\">\n<figure class=\"-auto-width\">\n<img alt=\"Grand Canyon village parking map shows parking lots 1-4, adjacent to the visitor center plaza, and A-D in the historic part of Grand Canyon Village.\" src=\"/grca/planyourvisit/images/parking_map_2-1200px-g_4.jpg?maxwidth=1300&amp;maxheight=1300&amp;autorotate=false&amp;format=webp\" title=\"The 3 parking highlighted by green arrows can accommodate RVs\"/>\n<figcaption>Parking lots 1-4 are at the Visitor Center. Parking lots A and B at Market Plaza. Parking lots C and D in the Village Historic District. </figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5488533\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5488533\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>RV Parking in Lot 1</strong> <strong>(Grand Canyon Visitor Center)</strong> – generally fills by 10:00 am</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>RV Parking in Lot B (Market Plaza) </strong>– generally fills by noon.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>RV Parking in Lot D</strong> <strong>(Backcountry Information Center in Village)</strong> – generally fills by 2:00 pm</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>From the RV parking lots,</strong> you can take a free <a href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/shuttle-buses.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=1914943,/grca/planyourvisit/shuttle-buses.htm,11006|\" onmouseout=\"\" onmouseover=\"\">shuttle bus</a> out to spectacular scenic views, or ride a shuttle around the South Rim Village.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5488541\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5488541\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h2>There is no RV parking in these lots:</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<h4><strong><span style=\"color:#FF0000;\">Please Do NOT park in lots 2, 3 or 4 or in lots A and C </span></strong></h4>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h4>Please Do NOT pull across multiple regular parking spaces</h4>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5488537\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5488537\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h2>Parking Your RV at Visitor Center Lot 1</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>From Lot 1,</strong> it is a short walk to the <a href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/grand-canyon-visitor-center.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=2230772,grand-canyon-visitor-center.htm,11006|\">Visitor Center</a> and canyon views at Mather Point.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>If you don't have a lot of time, and just want to see the canyon</strong>, take the short 5 minute walk <strong>(0.3 miles/ 0.48 km),</strong> to nearby <a href=\"/places/000/mather-point.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6645060,mather-point.htm,31100|\">Mather Point.</a><strong> </strong>Because it is close to the Visitor Center and parking lots, Mather Point is a busy scenic overlook.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>The <a href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/grand-canyon-visitor-center.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=2230772,grand-canyon-visitor-center.htm,11006|\">Visitor Center</a> has an information desk staffed by park rangers. <strong>Trip planning and hiking information</strong> is also available through <strong>signs and exhibits</strong> outside of the building. The Visitor Center Plaza also has the <a href=\"/places/000/grand-canyon-conservancy-park-store.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6645032,grand-canyon-conservancy-park-store.htm,31100|\">Park Store</a> offering a wide variety of books, maps, souvenirs, and gifts, a <strong>Passport Stamp Station </strong>and <strong>Junior Ranger Books/Badges. </strong>Bicycle rentals, a coffee bar, and grab-and-go food items are available from <a href=\"https://bikegrandcanyon.com/bike-rentals/rates/\" id=\"https://bikegrandcanyon.com/bike-rentals/rates/|\">Bright Angel Bicycles</a> </li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>From the <a href=\"/places/000/grand-canyon-visitor-center-shuttle-bus-terminal.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6645030,grand-canyon-visitor-center-shuttle-bus-terminal.htm,31100|\">Visitor Center shuttle bus terminal</a>, it is possible to ride the <a href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/village-blue-route.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6949515,village-blue-route.htm,11006|\">Village (Blue) Route</a> around the entire village that connects the Visitor Center to lodges, campgrounds, parking lots, the Backcountry Information Center, and <a href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/market-plaza-grca-south-rim.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6749361,market-plaza-grca-south-rim.htm,11006|\">Market Plaza</a> (store, 24 hour ATM, U.S. Post Office and Yavapai Lodge).<em> <strong>Scroll down for shuttle route map</strong></em><strong>.</strong> </li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>From the shuttle bus terminal, you can also ride the <a href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/covid-kaibab-orange-route-before-7-17-2021.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6595814,/grca/planyourvisit/covid-kaibab-orange-route-before-7-17-2021.htm,11006|\" onmouseout=\"\" onmouseover=\"\">Kaibab (Orange) Route</a> shuttle bus to <a href=\"/places/000/yavapai-geology-museum.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6645020,yavapai-geology-museum.htm,31100|\">Yavapai Geology Museum</a>, the <a href=\"/places/000/south-kaibab-trail.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6644877,south-kaibab-trail.htm,31100|\">South Kaibab Trailhead</a> and Yaki Point. You can return to the Visitor Center on the shuttle, or return by walking along the <a href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/upload/RimTrail.pdf\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=1910277|\">Canyon Rim Trail</a>. <strong><em>Scroll down for shuttle route map</em>.</strong><br/>\n<br/>\n<em><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\">(Note: there is no parking for private vehicles at the South Kaibab Trailhead or at Yaki Point. The only motorized access is by park shuttle bus).</span></em></li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_7359463\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_7359463\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h2>Parking Your RV in Village Lot B - Market Plaza</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.nps.gov/grca/planyourvisit/market-plaza-grca-south-rim.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6749361,market-plaza-grca-south-rim.htm,11006|\">Market Plaza</a> is at the center of Grand Canyon Village. <strong>RVs 30 feet and under can park here for the day. </strong></li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Here you will find <a data-remote=\"/common/commonspot/customcf/modals/modal_intercept.cfm?targetURL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.visitgrandcanyon.com%2Fdining-and-shopping%2Fcanyon-village-market-deli\" data-target=\"#myModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"https://www.visitgrandcanyon.com/dining-and-shopping/canyon-village-market-deli\" id=\"https://www.visitgrandcanyon.com/dining-and-shopping/canyon-village-market-deli|\">Canyon Village Market and Deli</a> (General Store), an outdoor <a href=\"/places/000/chase.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6648003,chase.htm,31100|\">ATM machine</a>, the <a href=\"/places/000/united-states-post-office.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6648001,united-states-post-office.htm,31100|\">U.S. Post Office</a>, and <a data-remote=\"/common/commonspot/customcf/modals/modal_intercept.cfm?targetURL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.visitgrandcanyon.com%2Fyavapai-lodge\" data-target=\"#myModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"https://www.visitgrandcanyon.com/yavapai-lodge\" id=\"https://www.visitgrandcanyon.com/yavapai-lodge|\">Yavapai Lodge</a> — with a gift shop, coffee bar, restaurant, and outdoor tavern.<br/>\n<br/>\nMarket Plaza is within walking distance of <a href=\"https://www.nps.gov/grca/planyourvisit/mather-campground-south-rim.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6774226,mather-campground-south-rim.htm,11006|\">Mather Campground</a> 0.2 mile/ 0.3 km and the adjacent <a data-remote=\"/common/commonspot/customcf/modals/modal_intercept.cfm?targetURL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.visitgrandcanyon.com%2Ftrailer-village-rv-park\" data-target=\"#myModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"https://www.visitgrandcanyon.com/trailer-village-rv-park\" id=\"https://www.visitgrandcanyon.com/trailer-village-rv-park|\">Trailer Village RV Park. </a>0.3 mile/ 0.5 km</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>For those who would like to walk along a paved greenway trail, Market Plaza is at the center of Grand Canyon Village, about 1 mile (1.6 km) from the <a href=\"/grca/learn/historyculture/historic-village.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6265783,historic-village.htm,14076|\">Village Historic District</a>, and <em>going in the opposite direction,</em> 1 mile (1.6 km) from the Visitor Center Plaza. </li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>The <a href=\"https://www.nps.gov/grca/planyourvisit/village-blue-route.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6949515,village-blue-route.htm,11006|\">Village (Blue) Route Shuttle &gt;</a> has westbound and eastbound stops here, and it can transport you to the Visitor Center Plaza/Mather Point, park lodges, campgrounds, the Historic District, and the Backcountry Information Center. <strong><em>Scroll down for shuttle route map</em>.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_7239786\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_7239786\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h2>Parking Your RV in Village Lot D</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Lot D is located on the west side of the village, near <a href=\"/places/000/maswik-lodge.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6644980,maswik-lodge.htm,31100|\">Maswik Lodge</a> and the <a href=\"/places/000/backcountry-information-center.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6644982,backcountry-information-center.htm,31100|\">Backcountry Information Center</a>. There are <a href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/village-blue-route.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6949515,village-blue-route.htm,11006|\">Village (Blue) Route</a> shuttle bus stops at both Maswik Lodge, and the Backcountry Information Center. From these stops, the buses head eastbound towards the campgounds, Market Plaza, and the Visitor Center Plaza. <strong><em>Scroll down for shuttle route map</em>.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>From Lot D</strong>, it is a <strong>0.4 mile/.65 km,</strong> walk to the <a href=\"/places/000/village-route-transfer-hermit-road-red-route.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6645076,village-route-transfer-hermit-road-red-route.htm,31100|\">Hermit Road Transfer Station</a>, where you can ride the <a href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/hermit-red-route.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=2665965,hermit-red-route.htm,11006|\">Hermit Road (Red) Route</a> shuttle and see spectacular scenic views along the <strong>7.5 mile</strong> <a href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/hermit-road.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=5899888,/grca/planyourvisit/hermit-road.htm,11006|\" onmouseout=\"\" onmouseover=\"\">Hermit Road</a>. <span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><em>Between March 1 and November 30, the shuttle provides the only free motorized access to Hermit Road.</em> </span><em><span style=\"color:null;\">During December, January and February, the shuttle is not in service, and Hermit Road is open to private vehicles under 22 feet..</span></em></li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>For those wanting to hike </strong><a href=\"/places/000/bright-angel-trailhead.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6644996,bright-angel-trailhead.htm,31100|\">Bright Angel Trail</a><strong>, </strong>the trailhead is just up the hill from the Hermit Road Transfer Station, (towards all the buildings).</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5488553\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5488553\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h2>South Rim Shuttle Bus Route Map </h2>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5488616\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5488616\"><div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup CaptionedImage\">\n<figure class=\"-auto-width\">\n<img alt=\"Map showing South Rim Grand Canyon Village and Vicinity showing three shuttle bus routes that are in service during the spring. The 4 routes are indicated by blue, orange purple and red lines.\" src=\"/grca/planyourvisit/images/South-Rim-Pocket-Map-3000-wide-copy-spring-2026.jpg?maxwidth=1300&amp;maxheight=1300&amp;autorotate=false&amp;format=webp\" title=\"\"/>\n<figcaption>This spring, 3 shuttle bus routes are in service from March 1, through May 22, 2026. Kaibab Rim (Orange) Route, shown on the right, transports visitors to S. Kaibab Trailhead, outstanding scenic views at Yaki Point, and Yavapai Geology Museum. Village (Blue) Route, center, connects the Visitor Center with lodges, campgrounds, Backcountry Information Center, and Market Plaza (general store and post office). Hermits Rest (Red) Route, on the left) follows a scenic road for exceptional canyon views. </figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5488525\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5488525\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<hr/>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5488479\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5488479\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h2>Tusayan - Park &amp; Ride Shuttle </h2>\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><b>IN SERVICE DURING SUMMER ONLY</b></span></p>\n<p>During summer months, the <strong><a href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/tusayan-route-purple.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6594987,tusayan-route-purple.htm,11006|\">Tusayan (Purple) Route</a></strong> provides free shuttle service between the gateway community of Tusayan and the NPS South Rim Visitor Center<br/>\n<br/>\n<em><strong>During the summer of 2026</strong>, RV visitors arriving midday will find parking in Tusayan, then riding the shuttle into the park is a better option —than entering the park and driving around looking for a parking spot, (especially during the busiest time of day: between 9:30 am and 4 pm).<br/>\n<br/>\n<strong>You must have valid park entrance pass to board the shuttle bus.</strong> </em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><em><strong><a href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/fees.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6714073,fees.htm,11006|\">Passes</a> </strong>may be purchased with cash or card, from several locations within the town of Tusayan. </em><br/>\n</li>\n<li><i>Entrance passes by also be <strong><a href=\"https://www.recreation.gov/sitepass/74282\" id=\"https://www.recreation.gov/sitepass/74282|\">purchased online</a></strong>. </i><br/>\n</li>\n<li><em>Bus stops at the IMAX Theater and the Grand Hotel in Tusayan have vending machines where you may purchase an entrance pass with your charge card. </em></li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n</td></tr>\n</table></div>\n</div><!-- col-sm-12 -->\n</div><!-- row -->\n</div><!-- ColumnMain col-sm-9 -->\n</div><!-- ColumnGrid row -->\n</div><!-- end container -->\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"ColumnGrid row\">\n<div class=\"ColumnMain col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12 text-content-size text-content-style\">\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">Last updated: March 1, 2026</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n <!-- ParkFooter -->\n<!--googleon: index-->\n\n</div><!-- end of <div main> -->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!-- the rest of the scripts are leftovers from before the centennial down and should be pared down where possible -->\n\n<link href=\"/common/commonspot/templates/assets/libs/colorbox/colorbox.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\"/>\n\n<div class=\"modal fade\" id=\"outdated-browser\" role=\"dialog\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n</div>\n</body>",
